Uses of Package
org.ensor.data.atom

  • Packages that use org.ensor.data.atom 
    Package Description
    org.ensor.data.atom
    This package holds objects which represent abstract data which can be serialized.
    org.ensor.data.atom.json
    This package contains serializers to convert the Dictionary and List structures into JSON and back again.
    org.ensor.data.atom.log
    This package contains utility classes to help with logging of the Atom, Dictionary, and List structures.
    org.ensor.data.atom.xml
    This package contains a serialzier for writing the dictionary and list objects to XML documents and reading them back again.
    org.ensor.threads.biote
    This package contains a thread handler for handling asynchronous activities.
  • Classes in org.ensor.data.atom used by org.ensor.data.atom 
    Class and Description
    Atom
    An atom is the primitive abstract data container for events.
    BoolAtom
    This is the primitive boolean data type.
    DictionaryAtom
    A dictionary is a name-value pair mapping for data.
    IDictionaryVisitable
    This class provides a mechanism for iterating dictionaries by providing a visitor.
    IDictionaryVisitor
    This interface provides a way for each element of a dictionary to be visited precisely one time.
    IListVisitable
    This method provides a way to call a method once for each of the elements of a list.
    IListVisitor
    This interface provides a way for each atom in a list to be visited precisely one time.
    ImmutableDict
    This class is an immutable version of the DictionaryAtom container.
    ImmutableList
    This class represents a list of immutable objects and the list itself is immutable.
    IntAtom
    An integer atom stores an integer.
    ListAtom
    This class represents a list of elements.
    RealAtom
    This class represents a floating point number.
    StringAtom
    This object is a string object wrapped in an Atom.
